cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the management of radio access networks (RANs) in mobile networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). It also involves the use of virtualization and network function descriptors, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and system and control theory (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a description model for managing RAN slices, which could be categorized under computer architecture (cs.AR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
